# Scratch / ad-hoc screenshots captured during ops or Playwright runs.
# Only the curated docs/screenshots/prod-*.png narrative set is committed;
# everything else is regenerable and must not be added by `git add -A`.
#
# Deny-by-default: ignore EVERYTHING under docs/screenshots/ and re-include
# only the curated prod-* narrative set. This makes the wrong outcome
# impossible - any stray ad-hoc / Playwright capture dropped into this folder
# is ignored automatically, so it can never be picked up by `git add -A`.
# To commit a new keeper, name it prod-<NN>-<surface>.png and reference it
# from a live .md (see the Doc Screenshot Hygiene Rule in copilot-instructions).
docs/screenshots/*
!docs/screenshots/prod-*.png
# Legacy scratch patterns kept explicit for clarity (covered by the wildcard).
docs/screenshots/scratch/
docs/screenshots/tmp-*.png
docs/screenshots/*.tmp.png
